AUDIENCE: That's the way to go.

00:32:26.530 --> 00:32:27.370
OLIVIA FOX CABANE: OK.

00:32:27.370 --> 00:32:29.036
Now, that's an answer,
it's really good.

00:32:29.036 --> 00:32:31.350
I hate silent retreats.

00:32:31.350 --> 00:32:34.640
But it's kind of like--

00:32:34.640 --> 00:32:37.250
meditation is training
for your mind.

00:32:37.250 --> 00:32:39.320
It's like going to
the gym for your mind.

00:32:39.320 --> 00:32:41.960
And usually by 2/3 of the way
into a meditation retreat,

00:32:41.960 --> 00:32:43.610
you are certain that
you are failing,

00:32:43.610 --> 00:32:45.380
the meditation
practice is failing,

00:32:45.380 --> 00:32:48.140
this whole idea is stupid, and
you want to go home anyway.

00:32:48.140 --> 00:32:49.880
And there is a certain
arc that you will

00:32:49.880 --> 00:32:52.580
see your own mind go through.

00:32:52.580 --> 00:32:54.230
The caveat that I
was going into is

00:32:54.230 --> 00:32:58.400
that meditation can, in
certain circumstances,

00:32:58.400 --> 00:32:59.840
help you through depression.

00:32:59.840 --> 00:33:03.200
It can also
precipitate depression.

00:33:03.200 --> 00:33:09.460
So as with any other tool, it's
useful to have good mentors,

00:33:09.460 --> 00:33:12.670
teachers, or-- and they can be
in the form of books, humans,

00:33:12.670 --> 00:33:13.510
it doesn't matter--

00:33:13.510 --> 00:33:15.010
but who can guide
you along the way,

00:33:15.010 --> 00:33:18.460
so you get sure that you don't
get stuck into a vicious cycle

00:33:18.460 --> 00:33:22.130
that through meditation can
actually worsen depression.

00:33:22.130 --> 00:33:24.739
Am I making sense, does anyone
have any questions, comments,

00:33:24.739 --> 00:33:25.530
objections, please?

